N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 9003.7 - Precluded investments

State Regulations

No contract or agreement entered into with a financial
organization may provide for the investment of any amounts under the plan in
any annuity contract providing for a term which could exceed five years or
which is measured by one or more natural lives or any life insurance or other
contract providing traditional death benefits. Notes
